Before completing UI copy work, verify:

- [ ] No em dashes (—) or en dashes (–) in UI text (except data placeholders)
- [ ] No conversational transitions
- [ ] No soft questions
- [ ] No motivational language
- [ ] Simple, declarative sentences
- [ ] Active voice used
- [ ] Sentence case for headers and titles
- [ ] Context-specific guidelines applied
- [ ] One idea per sentence
- [ ] Short paragraphs (3-4 sentences, maximum 5)

## Constraints

Agents MUST:
- Apply style guide rules to all UI copy
- Use sentence case for headers and titles
- Follow context-specific guidelines
- Verify compliance before completing work
- Fix violations when found

Agents MUST NOT:
- Use em dashes or en dashes in UI text (except data placeholders)
- Use conversational transitions
- Use soft questions
- Use motivational language
- Use title case for headers and titles
- Skip style guide validation

